\section{Proof}
In this section we prove Theorem~\ref{big}. Let $R, a, b, (\mu \mapsto G_{[\mu]})$ be given.
Assume $G_0 = a$ and $G_1 = a + b$.
Assume for every $\mu \in D$ and $m \ge 1$, that
\[ G_{[\mu m]} + G_{m} G_{[\mu]}  =  G_{[\mu]} G_{m}\eqno(\dagger)\]
Assume for every $n\ge 2$, \[n!G_{n} = \sum_{k = 1}^{n-1}{(n-1)!\over k! }\left(\left(\sum_{\lambda\in C^k_{n-1}} G_{[0\lambda]}\right) +
  \left(\sum_{\lambda\in C^k_n} \lambda(2)G_{[\lambda]}\right)\right)
\eqno(\ddagger)\]

Now define $\Z[x] = ax + xb$ and
\[X_n =  \sum_{k = 1}^n\sum_{\lambda \in C^k_n}{n!\over k!}G_\lambda\]
Notice that $X_1 = G_1 = \Z[1]$. Therefore if we can show $\Z[X_n] = X_{n+1}$, then we have
\[ \sum_{m=0}^n {n\choose m}a^mb^{n-m} = \Z^n[1] = X_n\]
as required.
